## Available Competitive Intelligence

- Competition description: `../research/description.md`
- 5 top kernel notebooks in `../research/kernels/`

data_findings.finding: bbox3.cpp optimizer uses: Complex Number Vector Coordination, Fluid Dynamics, Hinge Pivot, Density Gradient Flow, Global Boundary Tension. Key parameters: -n (iterations), -r (rounds). Uses aggressive_repair for overlap resolution with separation vectors.

tree_packer_v21.cpp uses: Swap moves, Multi-angle restarts, Higher temperature SA, Squeeze, Compaction, LocalSearch. Also includes backward propagation (bp.cpp) that removes trees from larger N configs to improve smaller N configs. Key parameters: -n (iterations), -r (rounds).

Pre-optimized submissions available at /home/nonroot/snapshots/santa-2025/21116303805/code/preoptimized/ including santa-2025.csv (score ~70.676), bbox3 binary, and multiple CSV files from various sources. Best ensemble score: 70.676102.
